   The Award

   Thirty-four or more scholarships are awarded annually which must be
   used at one of the seventeen 1890 Historically Black Land-Grant
   Institutions. Each award provides annual tuition, employment, employee
   benefits, use of a personal computer and software while on scholarship,
   fees, books, room and board for each of the 4 academic years. Each
   annual scholarship renewal is contingent upon satisfactory performance
   and normal progress toward the bachelors degree. Upon completion of
   the scholars academic degree program, there is an obligation of 1 year
   of service to the U.S. Department of Agriculture for each year of
   financial support.

